cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and image processing, specifically on the task of rain streak removal. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves modeling the motion blur mechanism of rain streaks, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper uses both synthetic and real data, indicating that it could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
